Western Cape Police have arrested three men in separate incidents on charges of attempted murder, possession of an unlicensed firearm and attempted hijacking. Police spokesperson Frederick Van Wyk says a man was arrested in Tafelsig, Mitchells Plain, after police responded to a shooting incident. Community members informed the police of the 49-year-old suspect’s whereabouts and he was found in possession of an unlicensed pistol and six rounds of ammunition. #sapsWC Mitchells Plain SAPS members arrested a 49-year-old suspect for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition and attempted murder in Laura Crescent, Tafelsig today. #GunsOffTheStreets MLhttps://t.co/bzrQ7EaynE pic.twitter.com/I0mdbKaARD — SA Police Service  (@SAPoliceService) January 19, 2021  In a separate incident, officers intervened when an e-hailing driver was being robbed in Browns Farm, Philippi. Two suspects tried to rob the driver of cash and his cellphone and were arrested on charges of attempted hijacking.